Youtube Widget 0.0.1 for the SilverStripe Blog Module
22.09.2008
By nivanka@whynotonline.com

Released under the BSD license. 

Extract this to your SilverStripe root directory and run "db/build", then visit your blog page and drag and drop the widget to activate. Fill the width, height, URL and the title (or a note for the video), To get the URL please follow the folliong instructions.

1.get the code from youtube.
2. find the param tag with the name movie
3. copy and paste the value of that param
